cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

The paper focuses on generating textual descriptions of short video clips using recurrent neural networks (RNN) and visual content classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also utilizes RNN-based language models, which falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of RNNs also involves training and optimization, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also utilizes dense trajectory video features, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval and natural language processing, which falls under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
